subfields.a: U. S. Chemical Warfare Service. Ann.rept. 1919/20 (not included in list of divisions)

The Medical Division of the Army's Chemical Warfare Service was established in 192-?; went out of existence in 193-?; reactivated in July 1943; name changed in 1946 to Medical Division of U. S. Chemical Corps; on Mar. 6, 1951, became the Medical Laboratories of the U. S. Chemical Corps; on Feb. 1, 1956, changed to U. S. Chemical Warfare Laboratories; on July 1, 1960 became Chemical Research and Development Laboratories.
